    {
      "beat_id": "B13",
      "t_start": 108,
      "estimated_duration_s": 22,
      "narration_text": "Electron, mass 9.11×10⁻³¹ kg, barrier height V₀ − E = 1 eV = 1.6×10⁻¹⁹ J. Decay constant κ = √(2mΔV)/ħ ≈ 5.1 nm⁻¹. Over 1 nm: probability density falls by e^{−10.2} ≈ 3.7×10⁻⁵. Small — but measurable by an STM.",
      "shot": {
